# PulseLoop Design System

## Aesthetic

Pure-neutral white, calm "life OS" feel. Inspired by Notion + Attio. No gradients on interactive elements. Monochrome iconography only (SF Symbols). Never use emoji characters in UI — always use `Image(systemName:)`.

## Colors (use `PulseColors.*`)

| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `.background` | Page/card surface (white) |
| `.canvas` | Slightly off-white page fill |
| `.fillSubtle` | Icon backgrounds, input fills, inactive pill |
| `.fillMuted` | Search bar background |
| `.borderHairline` | Card outlines (1pt) |
| `.borderStrong` | Button outlines, checkbox borders |
| `.textPrimary` | Headlines, body text, icons |
| `.textSecondary` | Supporting body text |
| `.textMuted` | Timestamps, placeholders, section labels |
| `.textFaint` | Disabled / decorative |
| `.accent` | Rare emphasis only (not for primary buttons) |

Primary action buttons use **`Color.black`** background with white text — not accent.

## Typography (use `PulseFont.*`)

- **Headings/greetings**: `PulseFont.title(28)` — Newsreader serif
- **Card titles**: `PulseFont.titleMedium(22)` — Newsreader medium
- **Section labels**: `PulseFont.bodyMedium(11)`, `.tracking(0.8)`, `.textMuted`, UPPERCASED
- **Body text**: `PulseFont.body(14–15)` — Hanken Grotesk regular
- **Buttons**: `PulseFont.bodySemibold(15)` — Hanken Grotesk semibold
- **Chips/badges**: `.system(size: 11–12)` or `PulseFont.bodyMedium(12)`
- **Micro labels**: `PulseFont.bodyMedium(11)`, tracked

## Spacing & Layout

- Page horizontal padding: **20px**
- Card internal padding: **16–20px**
- Card corner radius: **14–16px** (`.continuous`)
- Button height: **44px** (standard), **52px** (large onboarding)
- Button radius: **10–12px**
- Section vertical spacing: **10–14px**
- Inter-card spacing: **14px**

## Cards

```swift
.padding(16)
.background(PulseColors.background)
.clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 14, style: .continuous))
.overlay {
    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 14, style: .continuous)
        .stroke(PulseColors.borderHairline, lineWidth: 1)
}
```

Or use `PulseCard(padding:radius:)` for standard cards.

## Buttons

**Primary (black fill):**
```swift
Text("Start")
    .font(PulseFont.bodySemibold(15))
    .foregroundStyle(.white)
    .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)
    .frame(height: 44)
    .background(Color.black)
    .clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 12, style: .continuous))
```

**Secondary (outlined):**
```swift
Text("Not now")
    .font(PulseFont.bodySemibold(15))
    .foregroundStyle(PulseColors.textSecondary)
    .padding(.horizontal, 16)
    .frame(height: 44)
    .background(PulseColors.background)
    .clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 12, style: .continuous))
    .overlay {
        RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 12, style: .continuous)
            .stroke(PulseColors.borderStrong, lineWidth: 1)
    }
```

## Icons

- Always use **SF Symbols** — never emoji characters
- Icon backgrounds: `PulseColors.fillSubtle`, clipped to `RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 8)` or `Circle()`
- Icon weight: `.medium` for UI chrome, `.semibold` for emphasis
- Icon color: `PulseColors.textPrimary` (default) or `.textMuted` (secondary)

## Section Headers

```swift
Text("RIGHT NOW")
    .font(PulseFont.bodyMedium(11))
    .foregroundStyle(PulseColors.textMuted)
    .tracking(0.8)
```

## Task Rows

- Checkbox: 18x18 rounded rectangle (radius 6)
- Done state: black fill + white checkmark; strikethrough text in `.textMuted`
- Undone state: 1.5pt `borderStrong` stroke
- Chips: small rounded rect (radius 6), font size 11, colored background

## Tab Bar (BottomNavBar)

- 5 tabs: Home, Tracker, [AI center], Inbox, Friends
- Center button: black rounded rectangle (12pt radius) with white `sparkles` icon
- Tab icons: SF Symbols, outlined style, 20pt
- Active state: `textPrimary`; inactive: `textMuted`
- Bar background: `PulseColors.background` with `borderHairline` top stroke (0.5pt)

## Sheets / Modals

- Use `.presentationDetents` for half-height sheets
- Always include `.presentationDragIndicator(.visible)`
- Sheet background: `PulseColors.background`
- Sheet titles: left-aligned, bold, 22pt system font

## Navigation

- Use `NavigationStack` with `NavigationPath` for programmatic navigation
- Routes defined in `AppRoute` enum in `AppTheme.swift`
- Sidebar presented as `.sheet` from hamburger/avatar tap

## Voice Capture (fullScreenCover)

- Triggered from center AI button
- White background, "VOICE CAPTURE" tracked header, X close button
- Waveform bars synced to `VoiceServices.audioLevel`
- Stop button: black circle (72pt) with white rounded square inside

## Chat / Messenger

- Message bubbles: sent = black background + white text; received = `fillSubtle` + `textPrimary`
- Bubble radius: 18pt
- Input bar: `fillSubtle` rounded text field + "plus" button (share sheet) + circular send button
- Share sheet: 3-column grid of icon buttons on `fillSubtle` rounded squares (64x64, radius 16)

## Shared Components (compose these — never fork a one-off)

These live in `App/AppTheme.swift` and `DesignSystem/Components.swift`. Always reach for the shared primitive before hand-rolling a layout.

- **`HeroCard`** — the black "just one thing" next-action card. `eyebrow` + Newsreader `title` + optional `support`, plus filled `primary` and quiet `secondary` actions. Ink fill comes from `PulseColors.accent` (#161616 light / white dark) so it flips in dark mode. Use for the single most-important action on a screen. Don't draw a black `RoundedRectangle` by hand.
- **`IconTileRow`** — the canonical list row: SF-Symbol tile in `fillSubtle`, title + optional subtitle, optional trailing value, chevron when it has an `action`. Place inside a `PulseCard`; separate stacked rows with `IconTileRow.divider`. Rows with an `action` drill in — no dead rows.
- **`SegmentedControl`** — the one shared segmented control (Schedule/Protocol/Wellness, Category, Timing…). Gray `fillSubtle` track, white selected pill with soft shadow, `bodySemibold`. Generic over any `Hashable` via a `title` closure. Use this everywhere a segmented control appears; don't build per-screen variants.
- **`EmptyStateCard`** — designed empty state on the canonical card: neutral icon tile, Newsreader title, body, optional black CTA. Use on any data surface that can be empty instead of a bare "No data" label.
- **`SectionHeader`** (in `RootViews.swift`) / **`EyebrowLabel`** — uppercase, tracked, muted section labels with optional trailing action.

## General Rules

1. No emoji anywhere in rendered UI — use SF Symbols exclusively
2. No colored accent on primary buttons — use black (the `accent` token resolves to black/ink in light, white in dark)
3. Keep the interface "calm" — minimal color, generous whitespace
4. All interactive elements need `.buttonStyle(.plain)` when inside `NavigationLink` or `Button` wrappers to prevent default highlight
5. Section labels are always uppercase, tracked, and muted
6. Prefer `.system(size:weight:)` for one-off sizes; use `PulseFont.*` for body/title consistency
7. Cards always have hairline border — never rely on shadow alone
